{{Infobox Museum |name = Bob Marley Museum |image = 56hoperd.JPG |imagesize = 200 |caption = |alt = |map_type = Jamaica |map_caption = |map_alt = |coordinates = {{coord|18.019615|-76.779832|format=dms|display=inline,title}} |established = 1987 |dissolved = |location = 56 Hope Road, [[Kingston, Jamaica|Kingston]] 6, [[Jamaica]] |type = [[Historic house museum]] |collection = |visitors = |director = |curator = |publictransit = |network = |website = [http://www.bobmarleymuseum.com/ The Bob Marley Museum] }} The '''Bob Marley Museum''' is a [[museum]] in [[Kingston, Jamaica|Kingston]], [[Jamaica]], dedicated to the [[reggae]] [[musician]] [[Bob Marley]]. The museum is located at 56 Hope Road, Kingston 6, and is Bob Marley's former place of residence.{{citation needed|date=June 2017}} It was home to the [[Tuff Gong]] reggae record label which was founded by [[The Wailers (1963-1974 band)|The Wailers]] in 1970. In 1976, it was the site of a failed assassination attempt on Bob Marley.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://web.bobmarley.com/story/?storypage=6 |title=His Story - The Life and Legacy of Bob Marley |publisher=bobmarley.com |accessdate=2009-04-08}}</ref> The [[Chicago]]-based band 56 Hope Road takes its name in homage to the address.
